<subSubSection pageId="784" pageNumber="785" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="784" pageNumber="785">
Worldwide but excluding Europe and northern Africa, with about 165 species (Lorenz 2005: 445-447) arrayed in five genera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Aeolodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="784" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Aeolodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Andrewes (one Oriental species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Homethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="784" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Homethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Newman (ten australo-oriental species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Parascopodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="784" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Parascopodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Darlington (one Australian species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt-Goebel" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentagonica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="784" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Pentagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(about 85 species), and 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scopodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="784" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="784" pageNumber="785">Scopodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erichson (68 australo-oriental species). The Northern Hemisphere is underrepresented with only 17 species (about 10% of the world fauna).
</paragraph>
